# ğŸŒ¡ï¸ 739. Daily Temperatures  

## ğŸ”— Problem Link  
https://leetcode.com/problems/daily-temperatures/

---

## ğŸ“Œ Problem Summary  

You are given an array `temperatures` where `temperatures[i]` represents the temperature on the ith day.

For each day, find how many days you must wait until a warmer temperature.  
If no warmer day exists, put `0`.

---

## ğŸ§  Key Insight  

This is a **Next Greater Element** type problem.

We use a **monotonic decreasing stack** to track unresolved days.

The stack stores indices of days whose warmer temperature hasnâ€™t been found yet.

---

## ğŸš€ Optimal Approach (Monotonic Stack â€“ Right to Left)

### Idea:

Process the array from the **right side**.

For each day:

1. Remove all days from stack that are not warmer  
2. Top of stack gives next warmer day  
3. Distance = stack.peek() - current index  
4. Push current index  

---

## ğŸ’» Java Implementation  

```java
import java.util.Stack;

class Solution {
    public int[] dailyTemperatures(int[] temperatures) {
        Deque<int[]> st = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = temperatures.length;
        int res[] = new int[n];

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!st.isEmpty() && st.peek()[0]<=temperatures[i]){
                st.pop();
            }
            if(st.isEmpty()){
                res[i] = 0;
                st.push(new int[]{temperatures[i],i});
                continue;
            }

            res[i] = st.peek()[1]-i;
            st.push(new int[]{temperatures[i],i});
        } 

        return res;
    }
}
